<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Position 'right' property defines the offset from the right content edge of the parent box for relative positioning</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visuren.html#propdef-right" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="The 'right' property, for relative positioning, specifies the offset of the element in relation to the parent's right content edge." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #div1
            {
                background: blue;
                height: 1in;
                width: 1in;
            }
            div div
            {
                background: white;
                height: 0.5in;
                position: relative;
                right: 0;
                width: 0.5in;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is a box below with top-left corner missing.</p>
        <div id="div1">
            <div></div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>